Tabulation

t_mmrm_fixed.Rd

Tabulate the fixed effect estimates of an MMRM fit.

t_mmrm_fixed(object, format = "xx.xxxx")

Arguments

object

the MMRM model result produced by s_mmrm.
format

rtables format for the numbers other than degrees of freedom and p-values (default is "xx.xxxx").

Value

rtable object with the fixed effect estimates, standard errors, degrees of freedom, t-statistics, and p-values.

Examples

library(dplyr)
library(random.cdisc.data)

adsl <- radsl(cached = TRUE)
adqs <- radqs(cached = TRUE)
adqs_f <- adqs %>%
  dplyr::filter(PARAMCD=="FKSI-FWB" & !AVISIT %in% c("BASELINE")) %>%
  droplevels() %>%
  dplyr::mutate(ARM = factor(ARM, levels = c("B: Placebo", "A: Drug X", "C: Combination"))) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(AVISITN = rank(AVISITN) %>% as.factor() %>% as.numeric() %>% as.factor())

mmrm_results <- s_mmrm(
  vars = list(
    response = "AVAL",
    covariates = c("STRATA1", "BMRKR2"),
    id = "USUBJID",
    arm = "ARM",
    visit = "AVISIT"
  ),
  data = adqs_f,
  cor_struct = "random-quadratic",
  optimizer = "nloptwrap_bobyqa"
)
t_mmrm_fixed(mmrm_results)
